[2
Date: 9 Aug 2000
From: "Pig Disease Information Centre" <pdic@btinternet.com>
Subject: Swine Fever outbreak in U.K.
Sources: multiple, MAFF, and media

An outbreak of classical swine fever (CSF) has been confirmed on a Suffolk
pig finishing farm - the first outbreak in Britain since 1986. All 3 500
pigs have been destroyed. A 3km protection zone has been set up around the
infected premises. In this area movement of any pigs is banned. The source
of the outbreak is unknown as yet, but Ministry of Agriculture (MAFF)
officials are investigating other farms in Norfolk and Essex which are
linked to the infected farm. News updates and background information on CSF
can be found at <http://www.pighealth.com>.
---
Dr. Michael Meredith, Managing Director
Pig Disease Information Centre
<pdic@btinternet.com>
